org.codice.ddf.catalog.async.processingframework.impl

Class InMemoryProcessingFramework

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.codice.ddf.catalog.async.processingframework.impl.InMemoryProcessingFramework
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ProcessingFramework

    public class InMemoryProcessingFramework
extends Object
implements ProcessingFramework
    The InMemoryProcessingFramework processes requests using a thread pool and submits the results back to the CatalogFramework after processing is complete, when appropriate. If no changes are detected after processing, no results will be sent back to the CatalogFramework. Currently, partial updates are not supported, meaning that any results being returned by the InMemoryProcessingFramework will override the metadata in the catalog.
